==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water tender
<hw>Water tender</hw>. <fld>(Nav.)</fld> <def>In the United States navy,
a first-class petty officer in charge in a fireroom. He
⟦ldquo⟧tends⟦rdquo⟧ water to the boilers, sees that fires are properly
cleaned and stoked, etc. There is also a rating of <stype>chief water
tender</stype>, who is a chief petty officer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water thermometer</ent>⟦br⟧
